HEADWORD: Amphiprostyle
<hw>Am*phip"ro*style</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>amphiprostylos</ets>, Gr. <?/ having a double prostyle: cf. F.
<ets>amphiprostyle</ets>. See <er>Prostyle</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>Doubly prostyle; having columns at each end, but
not at the sides.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>An amphiprostyle
temple or edifice.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amphirhina</ent>⟦br⟧
